                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/atoc-540" class="program-course-title">
              ATOC 540 Synoptic Meteorology 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18540" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences              : Analysis of current meteorological data. Description of a geostrophic, hydrostatic atmosphere. Ageostrophic circulations and hydrostatic instabilities. Kinematic and thermodynamic methods of computing vertical motions. Tropical and extratropical condensation rates. Barotropic and equivalent barotropic atmospheres.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Eyad Hashem Atallah (Fall)                  </p>

    
